#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:2
msgid "# Theoretical"
msgstr "# Theoretical"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:4
msgid "## A cryptocurrency system"
msgstr "## A cryptocurrency system"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:6
msgid ""
"duniter uses the crypto-currency concept introduced by Bitcoin, which is to "
"use cryptography features such as _signature_ to create digital "
"currencies. duniter fits in this definition, however it has completely "
"different fundation principles than Bitcoin like Web of Trust and Universal "
"Dividend to do _really_ better than Bitcoin. Actually, duniter has a "
"theoretical reference called [Relative Money "
"Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/). This theory **demonstrates** that a "
"currency which aims at respecting each individual's economic liberties MUST "
"implement the Universal Dividend (aka. _Basic Income_), which is the only "
"way to avoid both spatial and temporal asymmetry toward money issuance."
msgstr ""
"duniter uses the crypto-currency concept introduced by Bitcoin, which is to "
"use cryptography features such as _signature_ to create digital currencies. "
"duniter fits in this definition, however it has completely different fundation "
"principles than Bitcoin like Web of Trust and Universal Dividend to do "
"_really_ better than Bitcoin. Actually, duniter has a theoretical reference "
"called [Relative Money Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/). This theory "
"**demonstrates** that a currency which aims at respecting each individual's "
"economic liberties MUST implement the Universal Dividend (aka. _Basic "
"Income_), which is the only way to avoid both spatial and temporal asymmetry "
"toward money issuance."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:8
msgid "## A space-time asymmetry"
msgstr "## A space-time asymmetry"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:10
msgid ""
"Space-time asymmetry refers to the relative access of individuals to newly "
"created money. Concretely, all existing currencies (2015) are both spatially "
"and temporally asymmetrical for their users. Let's take Bitcoin example to "
"understand why."
msgstr ""
"Space-time asymmetry refers to the relative access of individuals to newly "
"created money. Concretely, all existing currencies (2015) are both spatially "
"and temporally asymmetrical for their users. Let's take Bitcoin example to "
"understand why."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:12
msgid "### Spatially"
msgstr "### Spatially"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:14
msgid ""
"When new Bitcoins are created, _only some Bitcoin users_ (the miners) are "
"credited of brand new Bitcoins, while the others get nothing. **We believe "
"this is the first injustice.** However, some might say:"
msgstr ""
"When new Bitcoins are created, _only some Bitcoin users_ (the miners) are "
"credited of brand new Bitcoins, while the others get nothing. **We believe "
"this is the first injustice.** However, some might say:"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:16
msgid ""
"> <div class=\"ui message\">« but miners used their electricity and time to "
"get it! »</div>"
msgstr ""
"> <div class=\"ui message\">« but miners used their electricity and time to "
"get it! »</div>"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:18
msgid ""
"... we would answer this work _shouldn't have been rewarded by newly created "
"Bitcoins_. New Bitcoins should spread the whole Bitcoin community. Miners "
"should be rewared another way, not by money issuance. Of course, Bitcoin "
"can't create money through Basic Income since Bitcoin users are not strongly "
"identified, and one might benefit multiple times of money creation if he "
"owned several wallets. duniter get rid of this problem in its conception by "
"identifying its users and giving _the same amount to everyone_."
msgstr ""
"... we would answer this work _shouldn't have been rewarded by newly created "
"Bitcoins_. New Bitcoins should spread the whole Bitcoin community. Miners "
"should be rewared another way, not by money issuance. Of course, Bitcoin "
"can't create money through Basic Income since Bitcoin users are not strongly "
"identified, and one might benefit multiple times of money creation if he "
"owned several wallets. duniter get rid of this problem in its conception by "
"identifying its users and giving _the same amount to everyone_."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:20
msgid "### Temporally"
msgstr "### Temporally"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:22
msgid ""
"Bitcoin has a planned limit of 21 million BTC, which means less and less "
"bitcoins will be created over the time until 0 remains. So, once first "
"adopters will have mined every bitcoin, how will future joiners do to get "
"bitcoins? Answer is: just like Euros or Dollars. To get money you have to "
"work for the ones who already own it. **We believe this is the second "
"injustice.** Every member of a monetary community should be equal towards "
"money issuance, and get the same relative amount of new money over the time, "
"_even if he is a later adopter_. duniter aims at fixing this bug too by making "
"Universal Dividend _grow by the time_ according to precise rules allowing "
"members equality toward money issuance on a half-lifespan."
msgstr ""
"Bitcoin has a planned limit of 21 million BTC, which means less and less "
"bitcoins will be created over the time until 0 remains. So, once first "
"adopters will have mined every bitcoin, how will future joiners do to get "
"bitcoins? Answer is: just like Euros or Dollars. To get money you have to "
"work for the ones who already own it. **We believe this is the second "
"injustice.** Every member of a monetary community should be equal towards "
"money issuance, and get the same relative amount of new money over the time, "
"_even if he is a later adopter_. duniter aims at fixing this bug too by making "
"Universal Dividend _grow by the time_ according to precise rules allowing "
"members equality toward money issuance on a half-lifespan."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:24
msgid "## A solution"
msgstr "## A solution"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:26
msgid ""
"Idea is the following: Bitcoin has teached us _it is possible_ to create a "
"currency system allowing both to create digital money and to exchange it "
"without central authority. What we need to change is _the way money is "
"issued_ so we finally has a symmetrical system. We need Bitcoin + Universal "
"Dividend. But Universal Dividend _implies_ to have a community of identified "
"people. This is where Web of Trust (WoT) comes into place: this concept, "
"introduced by cryptography with OpenPGP format, allows us to identify people "
"in a decentralized manner. It works this way: each one creates _a personal "
"identity_, linked to its cyptographical certificate, which has to be "
"confirmed by others members using their own cryptographic key. It is that "
"simple: **people define by themselves who is part of the community and who "
"is not.**"
msgstr ""
"Idea is the following: Bitcoin has teached us _it is possible_ to create a "
"currency system allowing both to create digital money and to exchange it "
"without central authority. What we need to change is _the way money is "
"issued_ so we finally has a symmetrical system. We need Bitcoin + Universal "
"Dividend. But Universal Dividend _implies_ to have a community of identified "
"people. This is where Web of Trust (WoT) comes into place: this concept, "
"introduced by cryptography with OpenPGP format, allows us to identify people "
"in a decentralized manner. It works this way: each one creates _a personal "
"identity_, linked to its cyptographical certificate, which has to be "
"confirmed by others members using their own cryptographic key. It is that "
"simple: **people define by themselves who is part of the community and who "
"is not.**"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:28
msgid ""
"> duniter however won't use OpenPGP for its cryptographic features: Elliptic "
"Curves will be used instead for the conciseness of its generated keys and "
"the pratical advantages it results from. This involves for us to specify our "
"own Web of Trust mechanisms, but we think it worths the pain."
msgstr ""
"> duniter however won't use OpenPGP for its cryptographic features: Elliptic "
"Curves will be used instead for the conciseness of its generated keys and "
"the pratical advantages it results from. This involves for us to specify our "
"own Web of Trust mechanisms, but we think it worths the pain."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:30
msgid "### The Blockchain"
msgstr "### The Blockchain"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:32
msgid ""
"Bitcoin's blockchain mechanism is important for us for two main "
"reasons: **synchronization and security**. duniter will still use it to "
"benefit from these two features. However, duniter's blockchain is slightly "
"different: it not only stores transactions but _community variations_ for "
"defining the WoT. It also has a different _Proof-of-Work_ mechanism made "
"possible by WoT definition, providing **a really much more energy efficient "
"way** to compute the blockchain."
msgstr ""
"Bitcoin's blockchain mechanism is important for us for two main reasons: **"
"synchronization and security**. duniter will still use it to benefit from "
"these two features. However, duniter's blockchain is slightly different: it "
"not only stores transactions but _community variations_ for defining the "
"WoT. It also has a different _Proof-of-Work_ mechanism made possible by WoT "
"definition, providing **a really much more energy efficient way** to compute "
"the blockchain."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:34
msgid "#### Web of Trust"
msgstr "#### Web of Trust"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:36
msgid ""
"The Web of Trust is to be written in our common document: the "
"blockchain. Just the same way Bitcoin's transaction are written in Bitcoin's "
"blockchain, but for identity of people. Thus, blockchain constitutes a "
"_space-time referential_, where _space_ is represented by individuals and "
"_time_ provided by blockchain units: the blocks. What we finally have "
"is **wot(t)**: the community at a _t_ instant."
msgstr ""
"The Web of Trust is to be written in our common document: the blockchain. "
"Just the same way Bitcoin's transaction are written in Bitcoin's blockchain, "
"but for identity of people. Thus, blockchain constitutes a _space-time "
"referential_, where _space_ is represented by individuals and _time_ "
"provided by blockchain units: the blocks. What we finally have is **wot(t)**:"
" the community at a _t_ instant."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:38
msgid "#### Transactions"
msgstr "#### Transactions"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:40
msgid ""
"But that's not all: blockchain is also the place where _transactions_, the "
"support of money, are sequentially stored and allow to define money "
"ownership. For this part, duniter really looks like Bitcoin: transactions take "
"inputs (_a.k.a._ sources) and generate outputs. Transaction is a flow of "
"money. However, in duniter inputs may be:"
msgstr ""
"But that's not all: blockchain is also the place where _transactions_, the "
"support of money, are sequentially stored and allow to define money "
"ownership. For this part, duniter really looks like Bitcoin: transactions take "
"inputs (_a.k.a._ sources) and generate outputs. Transaction is a flow of "
"money. However, in duniter inputs may be:"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:43
msgid "money from another transaction [Bitcoin like]"
msgstr "money from another transaction [Bitcoin like]"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:43
msgid "money from a Universal Dividend [duniter specific]"
msgstr "money from a Universal Dividend [duniter specific]"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:45
msgid ""
"As you can see, no _generation transaction_ exists in duniter. This kind of "
"transaction is replaced by _Universal Dividend input_. Outputs, on their "
"side, are always public keys, and not necessarily WoT members' public "
"keys: _companies_ may also have public key. This lead us to an important "
"fact: **companies are also able to use the currency**."
msgstr ""
"As you can see, no _generation transaction_ exists in duniter. This kind of "
"transaction is replaced by _Universal Dividend input_. Outputs, on their "
"side, are always public keys, and not necessarily WoT members' public keys: "
"_companies_ may also have public key. This lead us to an important fact: **"
"companies are also able to use the currency**."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:47
msgid ""
"> Do note carefully that, even if they may participate, **companies won't be "
"able to create money**. Only individuals will able to do it. This is a very "
"important point."
msgstr ""
"> Do note carefully that, even if they may participate, **companies won't be "
"able to create money**. Only individuals will able to do it. This is a very "
"important point."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:49
msgid "#### Proof of Work"
msgstr "#### Proof of Work"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:51
msgid ""
"Like any P2P crypto-currency system, duniter has a way to synchronize its "
"peers for writing its common document (the blockchain). However, duniter's "
"benefiting from a really different environment than other altcoins: **an "
"identified Web of Trust**. This little difference has a tremendous impact: "
"while Bitcoin has to make a **global trial** using CPU resource to avoid "
"blockchain's hijacking by few people, duniter has the possibility to rely on "
"its members to write the blockchain: this allows us to both avoids the "
"energy wasting problem introduced by PoW & easily sweep away the 51% attack "
"in duniter. Concretely, duniter has a **personalized trial** for each of its "
"members that is getting harder for the member who succeeds writing a block, "
"while it is getting easier - until a given floor - for the others. This "
"mechanism ensures a rotation in the blockchain's writing, while keeping the "
"advantage of PoW for synchronizing the peers."
msgstr ""
"Like any P2P crypto-currency system, duniter has a way to synchronize its "
"peers for writing its common document (the blockchain). However, duniter's "
"benefiting from a really different environment than other altcoins: **an "
"identified Web of Trust**. This little difference has a tremendous impact: "
"while Bitcoin has to make a **global trial** using CPU resource to avoid "
"blockchain's hijacking by few people, duniter has the possibility to rely on "
"its members to write the blockchain: this allows us to both avoids the "
"energy wasting problem introduced by PoW & easily sweep away the 51% attack "
"in duniter. Concretely, duniter has a **personalized trial** for each of its "
"members that is getting harder for the member who succeeds writing a block, "
"while it is getting easier - until a given floor - for the others. This "
"mechanism ensures a rotation in the blockchain's writing, while keeping the "
"advantage of PoW for synchronizing the peers."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:53
msgid ""
"> It can be noted too that, since a block does not provide extra money "
"creation, members won't be pushed into competing for writing next block."
msgstr ""
"> It can be noted too that, since a block does not provide extra money "
"creation, members won't be pushed into competing for writing next block."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:55
msgid "### To summarize"
msgstr "### To summarize"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:57
msgid ""
"duniter's blockchain can be compared to Bitcoin's blockchain: a great book "
"tracing the history of each membership inside the Community along with the "
"transactions of its users. With the blockchain, we have the **fundamental "
"referential** of the [Relative Money Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/) "
"(humans), and the flow of transactions emitted by the currency users."
msgstr ""
"duniter's blockchain can be compared to Bitcoin's blockchain: a great book "
"tracing the history of each membership inside the Community along with the "
"transactions of its users. With the blockchain, we have the **fundamental "
"referential** of the [Relative Money Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/) "
"(humans), and the flow of transactions emitted by the currency users."

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:59
msgid "## A free economy"
msgstr "## A free economy"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:61
msgid ""
"The goal of all this is to allow people to participate to a _free economy_ "
"thanks to a _free currency_. What is a free economy? [Relative Money "
"Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/) defines it through 4 economic "
"freedoms:"
msgstr ""
"The goal of all this is to allow people to participate to a _free economy_ "
"thanks to a _free currency_. What is a free economy? [Relative Money "
"Theory](http://vit.free.fr/TRM/en_US/) defines it through 4 economic "
"freedoms:"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:66
msgid ""
"**The freedom to choose your currency system**: because money should not be "
"imposed"
msgstr ""
"**The freedom to choose your currency system**: because money should not be "
"imposed"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:66
msgid ""
"**The freedom to access resources**: because we _all_ should have access to "
"economic & monetary resources"
msgstr ""
"**The freedom to access resources**: because we _all_ should have access to "
"economic & monetary resources"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:66
msgid ""
"**The freedom to estimate & produce value**: because value is a purely "
"relative to each individual, in space and time"
msgstr ""
"**The freedom to estimate & produce value**: because value is a purely "
"relative to each individual, in space and time"

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:66
msgid ""
"**The freedom to trade with the money**: because we should not be limited by "
"the avaible money supply"
msgstr ""
"**The freedom to trade with the money**: because we should not be limited by "
"the avaible money supply"

#. type: Plain text
#: posts/2015-08-11-theoretical.md:67
msgid ""
"Those 4 economic freedoms should be understood together, not "
"exclusively. Plus, _\"freedom\"_ has to be understood as "
"\"_non-nuisance_\". So here, _freedom_ does not mean the right to take all "
"of a resource (like water source in a desert) so no more is available to the "
"others. Now you get it, this is the goal: _free economy through free "
"currency._"
msgstr ""
"Those 4 economic freedoms should be understood together, not exclusively. "
"Plus, _\"freedom\"_ has to be understood as \"_non-nuisance_\". So here, "
"_freedom_ does not mean the right to take all of a resource (like water "
"source in a desert) so no more is available to the others. Now you get it, "
"this is the goal: _free economy through free currency._"
